<h2>Track accessibility audits</h2>

<p>Accessibility audits are formal assessments of your product's accessibility compliance. Tracking audits helps you monitor audit history, costs, and outcomes.</p>

<h3>Adding an audit</h3>
<ol>
    <li>Navigate to <strong>Apps → Accessibility Issues and Statements</strong></li>
    <li>Select your enrolled product</li>
    <li>Go to the <strong>Audits</strong> tab</li>
    <li>Click <strong>Add Audit</strong></li>
    <li>Fill in the audit details:
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Audit Date:</strong> When the audit was conducted (required)</li>
            <li><strong>Audit Type:</strong> Type of audit (e.g., Internal, External, GDS Assessment)</li>
            <li><strong>Audited By:</strong> Who conducted the audit</li>
            <li><strong>Cost:</strong> Cost of the audit (optional)</li>
            <li><strong>Report URL:</strong> Link to the audit report (optional)</li>
            <li><strong>Notes:</strong> Additional information about the audit</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Click <strong>Save Audit</strong></li>
</ol>

<h3>Viewing audit history</h3>
<p>The <strong>Audits</strong> tab displays:</p>
<ul>
    <li>All audits in chronological order (most recent first)</li>
    <li>Audit date and type</li>
    <li>Who conducted the audit</li>
    <li>Cost information</li>
    <li>Links to audit reports</li>
    <li>Total audit spend for the product</li>
</ul>

<h3>Total audit spend</h3>
<p>The dashboard shows the total amount spent on accessibility audits across all products. This helps with:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Budget planning and tracking</li>
    <li>Understanding investment in accessibility</li>
    <li>Reporting to stakeholders</li>
</ul>

<h3>Best practices</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Record all audits, both internal and external</li>
    <li>Include costs for budget tracking</li>
    <li>Link to audit reports for easy reference</li>
    <li>Add notes about key findings or recommendations</li>
    <li>Update audit records if reports become available later</li>
</ul>

<h3>Using audit data</h3>
<p>Audit information helps you:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Track compliance improvements over time</li>
    <li>Identify recurring issues</li>
    <li>Plan future audit schedules</li>
    <li>Demonstrate commitment to accessibility</li>
    <li>Support business cases for accessibility investment</li>
</ul>

